name: Design house-city centre-private parking
description:
Your own modern house in the city center, surrounded by a courtyard. Both stations within walking distance and all public transport around the corner. Museums, beaches, theaters, shops, canals nearby. Bakery, supermarket and shops 2 min.
Private parking can be reserved in advance by owner, 15,00 euros per day.
neighborhood_overview: This neighborhood is great, students, expats and a lot of artist. Incredibly many and good restaurants, boat cafes on and along the canal. It is a special neighborhood, full of diversity of people. Chinatown is around the corner, the parliament 5 min. from your house and the bakery and supermarket around the corner. Many terraces and shops. if you want peace and tranquility, just 600 meters away you can walk into the forest and from there the beautiful dune area. You can rent bicycles on the canal, all within walking distance
host_about:
We are a friendly couple who live in the center of this beautiful city. Open-minded and easy going in life. We have a few trendy short Stay apartments right in the old city center of The Hague.  We are the place to stay When you are in need of accommodation. Whether it be for a business trip, an internship, a holiday or a transition period, we have plenty of possibilities. We have been around for a while and we know how to do things right. Service is our pleasure!

Our apartment is fully furnished, newly renovated and available for short term rentals Throughout the Year. Situated in the picturesque old city center of The Hague, within walking distance from both Central Station and Holland Spoor train station, it is the ideal 'home away from home'. Also within walking distance, one can find numerous at shops, grocery stores and restaurants. The all-in price includes furniture, fittings and fixtures, energy, water, internet connection, TV, service costs and a janitor. And of course there's a washing machine and a drier, pots and pans, bed linen, towels, a bathrobe, iron and ironing board, cups, plates and whatsoever.

name: Cute Room in  Den Haag Centrum
description:
Nice but small L-shaped room in 1920's era 3 bedroom portiek flat in Centrum.

Pease note II do have a security guard, Gato the cat and she is very sweet but if you have allergies or dont like cats.....

Room w bunk bed (single + double), dresser, desk + chair

Full kitchen, nice living room, bath w shower/ Jacuzzi, WIFI very quiet location with children's farm behind flat 10 min walk to Centrum & 10 min tram or bike ride to the beach
host_about:
I'm an American Expat with dual nationality living now 28 years in the Netherlands. I really enjoy the Netherlands as my adopted home country and have no plans to return to the US other than for visits.

On a personal level, I have three daughters 25 , 30 and 44 with the two youngest growing up in the Netherlands and attending Dutch schools. 

Two of the three lived in the US : Washington DC and New York ( but now Marseille)  

My 30 year old moved first back to Holland 8 years ago , then Brussels and now Helsinki and is active in the environmental movement .

My oldest owns a home in Williamsburg, Brooklyn ( now living in Marseille) and founded an environmental NGO 14+ years ago ( Human Impacts Institute) and has a  5 year old daughter.

Lastly my youngest moved to DC 2 years ago after graduating 5 years ago from College of Charleston with high honors in International relations and political science. 

You wouldn't be wrong to deduce that I'm quite proud of these three lovely ladies.

As for myself, I have traveled a lot over the last 40 + years for both work and pleasure and really enjoy meeting people so when I first heard of Airbnb almost 13  years ago, the concept of Airbnb appealed to me.

On a personal level, I have had an interesting career in high-tech international sales management. In my pleasure time I have quite varied interests but I am very much an outdoors person. I enjoy sailing, tennis, biking, camping, skiing etc. and I am as well a classical musician and a world class tournament bridge player. 

I have always loved to travel and meet people and have been doing just that since my teenage years when I hitchhiked with hair to my waist, a biker jacket and a backpack from Washington DC to San Francisco in the middle of the Hippy Era 1971 . ... can't say I regret it !!

Back to the present: 

I renovated my 3 bedroom flat in Centrum Den Haag 15 years ago when my two then teenage daughters still lived in the Netherlands and spent weekends with me. 

I then set up the two small bedrooms in my 3 bedroom flat with bunk beds to accomodate friends staying over.

Before I began hosting through Airbnb,  I occasionally rented  out a room to interns/foreign students and now have been hosting for the last 12 years through Airbnb. 

Hosting with Airbnb has been overall a very interesting and rewarding experience. 

I have found almost without exception my Airbnb guests from all over the world and from very differing backgrounds to be very interesting , considerate and nice to be around.

As you are now reading my profile, I hope that you will consider staying at my flat and I  look forward to welcoming you to my home and my adopted city of Den Haag.

Regards,

Paul

name: B&B The Hague, Own floor, Shared front door
description:
Peace and quiet, privacy, taste.

Bed and Bath


You have the sole use of a complete floor with 2 rooms within a stylish pre-war flat.
I live upstairs and only use the stairs, but I'm often absent.

NO kitchen.

If 2 persons only, you can use the masterbedroom for ‚Ç¨ 69,- / ‚Ç¨ 79,-.



Good bus connections.

No smoking!

Breakfast is not possible.
neighborhood_overview: Benoordenhout (the neigborhood where my B&B is) is a wonderfull quiet part of The Hague.
host_about:
Op mijn eigen reizen heb ik vaak gebruikt gemaakt van kleine B&B's.

De gastvrijheid, het persoonlijke contact en de kleinschaligheid heeft mij altijd aangetrokken.

Toen ik mijn appartement in Benoordenhout betrok, ben ik naar dit idee mijn eigen B & B gestart.

Ik heb een eigen atelier, waar ik werk aan schilderopdrachten.
Ik luister veel naar muziek, speel piano en zing in koren.

name: Family house nearby beach with private parking
description:
A modernly furnished family house with private parking:
- 5 minutes walk to the beach/boulevard
- 500m from the famous Pier of Scheveningen
- View of national dune Parc Meijendel
- With shops and many cozy restaurants around the cornery
-15 minutes by bike/car/public transport to The Hague Center
- Beautiful Westbroek parc (10 minutes walk)
Modern kitchen, 2 big bedrooms (2x2 beds), 2 toilets, 1 bathroom with bath, sunny garden/terrace with dining facilities, BBQ and trampoline.
neighborhood_overview: Our house is located on the edge of Scheveningen with a view of the dunes (Meijendel). A quiet neighborhood with and within walking distance of the beach/boulevard/entertainment. You can surf, relax on the beach, walk through the dunes, have a picnic in the park. Stroll along the boulevard with many restaurants (5 minutes walk) or enjoy a snack and a drink at one of the many beach bars (Black path). By tram you can reach the historic city center of The Hague with its many museums in 15 minutes. Visit the Girl with a Pearl Earring in the Mauritshuis or be amazed by M.C. Escher. The Binnenhof, the Peace Palace, Madurodam, Museon/Omniversum and Legoland are also nearby.
host_about: We live with our 11 year old daughter in this great house, 5 minutes walk from the beach of Scheveningen. At the weekend we enjoy nature or we make a cultural trip. We like to walk in the dunes, picnic in the park or go surfing or swimming in the sea. The Hague has a wide range of culture. Think of music (festivals) or visit a museum such as Escher in the Palace, the Museon or the Mauritshuis. Also nice for children. Within 5 minutes you stand with your feet on the beach and within 15 minutes in the city center. A great combination!

name: Beautiful vintage guesthouse
description: Spacious and light apartment in a beautiful and newly renovated mansion located in Belgisch Park, one of the oldest and nicest neighborhoods in the heart of Scheveningen. Ideal for exploring The Hague and Scheveningen. Our place is walking distance from beach and boulevard. Shops and restaurants are diverse and close at hand. Easy access to public transportation with direct lines to central station and The Hague city centre. Free parking is available on private property.
neighborhood_overview: Belgisch Park is one of the oldest and nicest neighborhoods in Scheveningen and The Hague. The area dates back to the late 1800's / early 1900's and offers a beautiful variety of Victorian type houses. It is a quiet and peaceful neighborhood ideally situated between the beach, city centre and Westbroek park. Supermarket, grocery shops, bakery, butchery and other shops for your daily needs are near by.
host_about:
We are a friendly and easy going Dutch couple who have lived abroad as well. We enjoy hospitality, home made food, traveling, the beach, all sorts of music and life in general. We live in The Hague for over 15 years and love the combination of city buzz and beach life. We have 3 girls of 6, 4 and 2.. 

Our home is an eclectic mixture of vintage curiosa and design. The top floor guesthouse is spacious, light and private, you have the whole floor to yourself. Ideal for a visit to The Hague and Scheveningen Beach. If you like a bit of retro and vintage design you will certainly feel at home  in our cosy guesthouse. 

We do our best to make our guest feel at home during their stay.  Looking forward to welcome you!

name: Infrared ligjt for more comfort
description:
This small room is cozy. The balcony is comfortable and and offers a nice view. This room is on the quiet side. In the morning you will wake up by singing birds.
Despite its small size, 3 people can sleep in this room furnished with a bunk bed: 1 above and two underneath. Of course you have to love each other if you want to experience this cozy sleep. Fortunately, I hear enough positive experiences. Love exists ;-)
neighborhood_overview:
This place has a lot of possibilities in the middle of the city. You are right in the center with all the possibilities and sights around. Within a 5-minute walk you are in the palace garden (Paleistuin) and you will see our King's Palace while enjoying a walk in this garden. Behind the palace garden is the Royal stables which are open to the public on certain days. On the other side of the Peleistuin is the famous Noordeinde street with attractive shops for the sophisticated taste and on the other hand with endless numbers of pupil-inspiring galleries.

Within a 10-minute walk you will find the Escher Museum and enjoy its beautiful paintings in its detailed style with love for nature.

Panoramamesdag can not be missed either. Indulge all your senses through the greatest painting in the world.

The best of Dutch painting of the Golden Age is of course in Mauritshuis (5 minutes walking distance from your stay location).

The Binnenhof is the ol
host_about:
OVER MEZELF
Ik ben geboren in Oekra√Øne en ben trots op mijn moederland. Sinds 16 jaar geleden woon ik in Nederland (ingeschreven op november 2015) en ben dol op de mogelijkheden die dit (ik noem het mijn) vaderland aan mensen kan bieden. Vriendelijkheid, hardwerkende mentaliteit en discipline spreken me erg aan in Nederland. Ik hou even veel van die 2 prachtige landen.

WELKOM
In mijn huis voel je je gelijk op je gemak. Voel je je thuis en vergeet niet dat je op bezoek bent is mijn motto.

HET KOKEN IN HUIS OF BUITEN HUIS OM ETEN
Het delen van keuken en eetkamer gaat hier in samenwerking met elkaar. Ik kook op vaste tijdstippen: vaak om 17:00 uur. De tijd er voor of er na kan gebruikt worden voor het bereiden van je eigen maaltijd. Het halen van een lekker buitenlands gerecht is hier makkelijk te doen. Grieks, Perzisch, Turks (Istanbul), Chinees, Indisch (Ramna), Italiaans, Japans, Surinaams, Afrikaans en natuurlijk Nederlands eten is hier vaak op 5 minuten loopafstand / makkelijk te vinden.

KOFFIE EN THEELIEFHEBBERS
Voor koffieliefhebbers is Florencia (Italian Icecream) voor de deur. Coffie Company is weer te vinden op 250 meter loopafstand van huis terwijl Boon (koffiebranderij) met verschillende soorten koffie uit verschillende landen  zich op maar 50 meter loopafstand bevindt. Het bezoeken van Lola Bikes & Coffee aan het Noordeinde zorgt zonder meer voor een onvergetelijke ervaring. 
Natuurlijk kan je ook een bakkie koffie thuis zetten met Bialetti Moka Induction mokapot voor 3 kops. Zowel koffie als thee is gratis voor gebruik. 

AUTO PARKEREN
Voor mensen die laat komen of het te druk hebben met hun planning kan geheel kosteloos een bezoekers parkeerkaart gebruikt worden. Deze kaart heeft een beperkt aantal uren dus voor mensen met meer tijd is er mogelijkheid om hun auto ook gratis te parkeren op 15 minuten loopafstand van mijn huis met uitzicht op leuke bezienswaardigheden zoals Vredespaleis, Anna Paulona-straat, Koninklijke stallen en de Paleistuin.

name: Waanzinnig uitzicht over zee!!!
description:
Our beautiful and comfortable studio - in the formerly famous ‚ÄúHotel Bord de la Mer‚Äù is on the edge of the North Sea.

From the first floor there is a great view from the Port of Scheveningen to the Pier and beyond.

In 2023, the kitchen and bathroom have been renewed, while maintaining charm. The bathroom has since been equipped with a walk-in shower.

neighborhood_overview: The place is unique to Scheveningen. The studio is located in the monumental building of Hotel Bord de la Mer from 1912. The Keizerstraat is around the corner, where, among other things, it is commemorated every year that later King William I returned to the Netherlands on 30 November 1813 with an English frigate as prince (the Prince's landing) and stayed at number 58. On the Keizerstraat are now all shops (the warm bakery/ cheese specialist / Albert Heijn / Hema / Kruidvat) and also the most cozy restaurants are a 2-minute walk from the rstudio. Start your day and breakfast in a beach pavilion. Rent a bike nearby and cycle to Meijendel and/or Katwijk and discover the Dune area around Wassenaar. Have dinner at 'Simonis' or go to food village at fe renewed pier and end the day at Crazy Pianos.

It's great to walk in the dunes and beach and stop for a drink at one of the beach clubs, which are available April through end October. In winter time, if we go for a walk at the beach, we warm up at one of the restaurants at one of the boulevards in Kijkduin or Scheveningen, which are open all year, or simply end up in de City Center.

We like to work out creative ideas for our house and bring them to reality. With this in mind we designed and built our studio and part of our furniture and hope that you will enjoy it as much as we do.

If you love people in all their qualities,from different countries with their habits and customs, it's great to browse through their shops or enjoy a delicious massage Turkish neck massage at the hairdresser who sets your ear hair on fire, then you've definitely come to the right place.
The apartment complex dates from the 1930s and was designed by Dirk Roosenburg, a prominent Dutch architect, a pupil of the famous architect Berlage. name: Nice cottage at the beach
description: Cozy house with sunny front and backyard. It's a fun and friendly neighborhood. Near a shopping street with varied shops. Both the beach and the center are only ten minutes by bike.
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is located near the beach. It is a street with many shops and lunch options, it calls 'the Fahrenheitstraat'. You can visit the town museum and cycling to the Omniverse and Frederick Henry Street is a nice shopping area ten minutes away and of course you have to see the beach every day . The beach club 'strandtent op palen' in Monster is a nice place to go to . So also when you start your walking at beach club 'parker Beach' and go to the left, you can walk along a very beauiful part of the beach, the name is  'de zandmotor'. Their are a lot of kite surfers and view is very special. The bicycle path along the coast from Kijkduin to 'Hoek van Holland' is very beautiful. In the center of The Hague is also much to experience fun , a boat ride to the Ooievaart is quite nice and the Courtyard ('binnenhof'). The shopping area the 'denneweg'  with all the antique shops and on their is a square with nice cafes and entertainment in the evening.
host_about: I'm very happy with my family, my husband Frank and  our two adult children Merel en Jelle. I prefer to be outside all day, rain or shine. Preferably on the beach for a long walks or to exercise. It's always nice to hear the sea and watch the beautiful skies.  Love spontaneous things with friends, gardening and cooking.

name: Fully equipped flat near the beach of The Hague!
description:
My modern and cozily furnished apartment is in a nice neighborhood in Den Haag Zuid. I always call the dunes and the beach my backyard ;-)
The location is very central. In direct surroundings you will find cozy lunch rooms, supermarkets, bars and various shops. The city center of The Hague can be reached very quickly and easily by bike or by public transport. An ideal base for a weekend away. A longer stay and/or discount for cash payment is certainly possible.
neighborhood_overview:
A reasonably quiet neighborhood, close to the beach & dunes. In the direct surroundings (Appelstraat and Vlierboomstraat) you will find various shops and restaurants such as a bakery, vegetable farmer, evening shop, neighborhood supermarket and restaurant Appels & Peren. It is possible to park nearby free of charge. All the details can be found in my apartment. Directly in front of the door is daily paid parking from 18.00 to midnight.

The spacious shopping centre with free parking on Savornin Lohmanplein (including an Albert Heijn, Aldi, cheese farmer, Gall&Gall, Hema & drugstore) is just 700 metres away.

The Reinkenstraat is also a very cozy street with various catering establishments, but for that you really need public transport, car or bicycle.

In the travel guide you will find all my favorite locations in the area.
host_about:
Een sportieve, vrolijke vrouw die positief in het leven staat. Life's good is mijn motto ;-)
Ik houd van uitgaan, wijntjes drinken en lekker koken & eten. Om in balans te blijven sport ik bijna dagelijks: racefietsen, fitness, een rondje hardlopen over het strand en door de duinen.... Heerlijk! Natuurlijk ga ik ook graag op vakantie. Wintersport, weekendjes weg, een actieve fietsvakantie of gezellig met vriendinnen naar Ibiza; het kan allemaal!

Omdat ik in de weekenden vaak elders verblijf, verhuur ik mijn heerlijke appartement graag aan levensgenieters zoals ik. Het is modern ingericht, ruim, licht en van alle gemakken voorzien. Het strand en de duinen noem ik altijd mijn achtertuin; je bent er namelijk zo!

neighborhood_overview:
This place has a lot of possibilities in the middle of the city. You are right in the center with all the possibilities and sights around. Within a 5-minute walk you are in the palace garden (Paleistuin) and you will see our King's Palace while enjoying a walk in this garden. Behind the palace garden is the Royal stables which are open to the public on certain days. On the other side of the Peleistuin is the famous Noordeinde street with attractive shops for the sophisticated taste and on the other hand with endless numbers of pupil-inspiring galleries.

Within a 10-minute walk you will find the Escher Museum and enjoy its beautiful paintings in its detailed style with love for nature.

Panoramamesdag can not be missed either. Indulge all your senses through the greatest painting in the world.

The best of Dutch painting of the Golden Age is of course in Mauritshuis (5 minutes walking distance from your stay location).

The Binnenhof is the ol
host_about:
OVER MEZELF
Ik ben geboren in Oekra√Øne en ben trots op mijn moederland. Sinds 16 jaar geleden woon ik in Nederland (ingeschreven op november 2015) en ben dol op de mogelijkheden die dit (ik noem het mijn) vaderland aan mensen kan bieden. Vriendelijkheid, hardwerkende mentaliteit en discipline spreken me erg aan in Nederland. Ik hou even veel van die 2 prachtige landen.

WELKOM
In mijn huis voel je je gelijk op je gemak. Voel je je thuis en vergeet niet dat je op bezoek bent is mijn motto.

HET KOKEN IN HUIS OF BUITEN HUIS OM ETEN
Het delen van keuken en eetkamer gaat hier in samenwerking met elkaar. Ik kook op vaste tijdstippen: vaak om 17:00 uur. De tijd er voor of er na kan gebruikt worden voor het bereiden van je eigen maaltijd. Het halen van een lekker buitenlands gerecht is hier makkelijk te doen. Grieks, Perzisch, Turks (Istanbul), Chinees, Indisch (Ramna), Italiaans, Japans, Surinaams, Afrikaans en natuurlijk Nederlands eten is hier vaak op 5 minuten loopafstand / makkelijk te vinden.

KOFFIE EN THEELIEFHEBBERS
Voor koffieliefhebbers is Florencia (Italian Icecream) voor de deur. Coffie Company is weer te vinden op 250 meter loopafstand van huis terwijl Boon (koffiebranderij) met verschillende soorten koffie uit verschillende landen  zich op maar 50 meter loopafstand bevindt. Het bezoeken van Lola Bikes & Coffee aan het Noordeinde zorgt zonder meer voor een onvergetelijke ervaring. 
Natuurlijk kan je ook een bakkie koffie thuis zetten met Bialetti Moka Induction mokapot voor 3 kops. Zowel koffie als thee is gratis voor gebruik. 

AUTO PARKEREN
Voor mensen die laat komen of het te druk hebben met hun planning kan geheel kosteloos een bezoekers parkeerkaart gebruikt worden. Deze kaart heeft een beperkt aantal uren dus voor mensen met meer tijd is er mogelijkheid om hun auto ook gratis te parkeren op 15 minuten loopafstand van mijn huis met uitzicht op leuke bezienswaardigheden zoals Vredespaleis, Anna Paulona-straat, Koninklijke stallen en de Paleistuin.

host_about:
Den Haag is een heerlijke stad om te wonen. Afkomstig uit een klein dorp in Friesland woon ik al weer 25 jaar in Den Haag. Een stad met internationale allure, maar dorps tegelijk en het strand is nooit ver weg! Het appartement (wat ik dus niet zelf bewoon) maakt onderdeel uit van mijn ruime Haagse portiekwoning (1933), waardoor ik de gelegenheid heb om jullie gastvrij te ontvangen en te laten ervaren waarom dit zo'n fijne plek is. Zelf ben ik vaak te vinden in de duinen of het strand, lekker uitwaaien of zonnebaden, een drankje op het terras van een gezellige strandtent of op de boulevard van Kijkduin of Scheveningen.

Hi, I'm Nienke and I live already over 25 years in The Haque, a beautiful city, with a lot of history, the beach and easy to reach the rest of Holland by Public Transport. I'll  be happy to have you as my guests and  will do my best to make your stay as comfortable as possible, so you'll be having a wonderful time.

name: Spacious house, centre The Hague, garden
description: Wonderful spacious house with sunny garden in 17th century area of The Hague. Walking distance to restaurants, Houses of Parliament, (film)theaters, museums and the main Hague shopping area. The garden has an entrance to 'Spinoza Alley', which leads to a classical Dutch canal. To get to the beach takes you 20 minutes by public transport. Free use of bicycles. Both main train stations at 800 meter, every 15 min train to Amsterdam (45 min).
neighborhood_overview:
In the historic area of The Hague there are several royal palaces, both Houses of Parliament and the Knights Hall at the Binnenhof, the 'Hofvijver' and famous museums including The Mauritshuis and Escher Museum. Also in the direct neighbourhood: many good restaurants and bars, (film)theaters and shops. The Hague's Chinatown is around the corner, in the Wagenstraat. The entrances of the neighbourhood are marked with two huge Chinese gates with sculptured dragons.
The area used to be the Jewish quarter of The Hague. After a revamp by the municipality since the 1970s it became a very popular urban area.

World Forum ( International convention centre ), Madurodam, Gemeentemuseum, Peace Palace, Parliament Buildings, the station and several other museums, restaurants and shops are easily accessible by public transport or bike.

For a nice lunch or diner you can walk to the harbor of Scheveningen (10 min), the Kurhaus with the boulevard and the shopping area the Palace Promenade is a 15 min walk or by public transport accessible.

Favourite restaurants are pastanini on the Fred, Stone by BLT and Vlaamsch Broodhuys. The port offers some good places too, like Lemon Grass, (pricey but great food and wines) and Burgerss. Public transport is great.

I love the fact that we live close to the beach, surrounded by green, but yet close to down town. But I also enjoy travelling to Africa again! I love to read (feel free to choose from the English books in our library) and cook. My motto in life is: treat others as you wish to be treated yourself. Looking forward to meeting you!

neighborhood_overview:
The beach of Kijkduin is quiet and clean and there are extensive dunes for walking and cycling. Kijkduin is located on the long-distance cycle path LF1. Via this route you cycle through the dunes to Scheveningen or in the other direction to Hoek van Holland and the Port of Rotterdam.

Skinboarders, kiters, golfers and windsurfers have found the Sand Motorcycle in the peninsula an ideal place to practice their sport. Scientists are investigating how the Sand Engine is developing to determine whether this innovative method of coastal protection is working. The Sand Engine is freely accessible to everyone. Visitors can hike along the vast sandy plain where seals regularly find their way.

Kijkduin offers plenty of opportunities to have a nice and cozy meal outside the door throughout the year. From March to October there are many beach pavilions on the beach. Our favorite is Blow on the nearest beach (beach stroke 1).

In the winter months there is plenty

name: Gorgeous 17th century canal house, city centre
description: Enjoy all the pleasures of this spacious, quiet and delightful canal house in the centre of The Hague‚Äôs city life. A central location, on the most beautiful canal of The Hague, also known as 'Avenue Culinair' due to the many charming high quality restaurants situated here. The city centre and the international train station can be reached within a five minute walk. Numerous shops, boutiques, restaurants and cafes are just around the corner. All this makes the house a unique place to stay.
neighborhood_overview: For centuries, this neighbourhood is the home and workplace of many artists and free spirits. The house where the philosopher Spinoza lived is just around the corner. Three master painters of the Golden Age, Paulus Potter, Jan van Goyen and Jan Steen lived and worked from the Dunne Bierkade (opposite the apartment), the place where beer was delivered into the city. You can still enjoy a beer here, cosy establishments can be found along the old routes of the canal boats, with appropriate names like De Pakschuit or De Paas. The canals and old avenues are being restored more and more. You can embark on a boat cruise of The Hague or the neighbouring municipalities. Those who like to discover on their own can hire canoes and explore the waterways themselves.
host_about: My name is Marjan and I'm living together with my husband and son in a 17th century house canal in The Hague city centre. My daughter is moved out already and she is studying Architecture in Belgium. We love to go out for dinner, to enjoy the sunset at the beach, to cycle in the dunes or to stay at home and prepare an excellent meal for friends. I love cooking, fine arts, reading, styling interiors, visiting antique and flea markets and travelling around. Futhermore I work in Amsterdam as a brand strategist and I travel by train in just 45 minutes to my office in the middle of the city center of Amsterdam. We look forward to welcome you!

description: 1 minute walk from the beach. Cozy neighborhood located in old Scheveningen. The old fisher houses were built in 1875 and have a unique atmosphere.
neighborhood_overview: The old fisherman's house is centrally located in Oud Scheveningen. On one side is the cave harbour with fishing boats, on the other is the Meijendel National Park where you can enjoy the peace and the unique flora and fauna. Only 1 minute walk from the house you can reach the beach. Here you can take a walk along the boulevard of Scheveningen. There is a cozy atmosphere with plenty of recreational opportunities due to the large amount of beach tents, shops, attractions and cultural events. The centre of The Hague can be reached within 10 minutes. There is also the possibility for the athletic Airbnb guest to rent a surfboard or take a surf lesson.

name: Studio with balcony in Statenkwartier
description:
A very light and cozy studio, on the upper floor of our house. It's spacious, and with a stylish interior. The studio has it's own kitchen, a bathroom and a sunny balcony.

The apartment is located in a beautiful early-20st century residential, green neighbourhood. There are many shops and some bars/restaurants just around the corner. Beaches, dunes and the Scheveningse harbour are on a 12-30 minutes walking distance. World Forum and musea are nearby; just as good public transport facilities.
neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is a residential area near the see and the beaches of Scheveningen. Also harbour and boulevard are nearby. Just around the corner there is the shopping street with shops for food, clothes, flowers and books, just as good restaurants and bars. The World forum with international congresses and performances is on 5 minutes walking. By tram 16 or by bicycle you can go the center of The Haghe. name: Spacious and sunny apartment near the beach
description:
This sunny, spacious private floor has its own livingroom with a balcony, a pantry microwave), a big bedroom with adjacent bathroom.

The apartment is perfectly situated in The Hague's old "Statenkwartier" (Scheveningen) and is a great base for cycling trips, hikes and cultural activities. The harbour, the beach and nice restaurants are close by.

The tram stops right around the corner and brings you to the city-center within several minutes. The beach is only a 14 minute walk away.
neighborhood_overview:
The Hague's "Statenkwartier" is known for its international ambiance. The beach is always within walking distance, as are several renowned museums and some of the most authentic shops in The Hague. Nice restaurants are never far away with both the harbour and the "Fred" (Frederk Hendriklaan) at less than 300 meters.

Some highlights in the area:
- The Gemeentemuseum
- The International Court of Justice
- The World Forum
- The Circus Theater (Musicals)
- The Omniversum
- GEM (Museum of photography)
- Museum Beelden aan zee (sculptures at sea)
- The old town of Scheveningen
- Hikes in the dunes
- Swimming at sea!
host_about: Wij wonen al 35  jaar met veel plezier in het Statenkwartier, daarvoor studeerden wij in Den Haag. Aad is Fysiotherapeut en leraar lichamelijke opvoeding, Inge is lerares lichamelijke opvoeding. Nu zijn we met pensioen. We houden van tennissen, wandelen  en lezen graag. We reizen veel, vooral met de fiets waarbij Azi√´ op de 1e plaats komt. We vinden het dan leuk andere mensen te ontmoeten.  Dus een Airbnb beginnen met onze geheel vrije etage was een logische stap. Elke gast moet zich op zijn gemak voelen: de een door veel contact te hebben, de ander door zijn eigen gang te gaan. Fijn dat wij als verhuurder kunnen bijdragen aan een goed verblijf in het Statenkwartier

description:

host_about:
Wij zijn Annemarie en Michiel Pronk en we heten je van harte welkom in onze Bed and Brownies 'In de werkplaats'. Die naam behoeft wel wat uitleg:  In 2016 won ik (Annemarie) 'Heel Holland Bakt', een fantastische en onvergetelijke ervaring! En tegelijkertijd een start van een periode van nieuwe kansen en mogelijkheden. Voor mij het moment om een aantal dromen waar te gaan maken. Waaronder het organiseren van bakworkshops, maar ook het realiseren van deze 'Bed and Brownies'. In de door Michiel compleet verbouwde, oude timmermanswerkplaats van mijn schoonvader, ontvangen wij je graag voor een heerlijk verblijf. Wij wonen met onze kinderen direct naast de studio en zijn zoveel mogelijk beschikbaar voor jullie vragen of een gezellig praatje, al kan je je natuurlijk ook lekker terugtrekken. De studio is splinternieuw, met prachtige nieuwe keuken en badkamer, vloerverwarming en elektrische aupingbedden voor een heerlijke nachtrust. De Bed and Brownies ligt direct achter de gezellige jachthaven in Scheveningen. Ook het strand en de duinen bevinden zich op loopafstand. Ontbijt kun je zelf verzorgen in de compleet uitgeruste keuken of kun je nuttigen in een van de restaurants in de buurt aan de haven of in de gezellige winkelstraat de Frederik Hendriklaan! Geen B dus van Breakfast, maar van Brownies, want uiteraard zorg ik voor een heerlijk zelfgebakken lekkernij bij aankomst. 
We zien er naar uit je te ontmoeten. Van Harte Welkom!

We are Annemarie and Michiel Pronk and we would like to welcome you to our Bed and Brownies 'In de werkplaats'. That name needs some explanation: In 2016 
I (Annemarie) won de Dutch version of 'The Great Britisch Bake off':  'Heel Holland Bakt', a fantastic and unforgettable experience! And at the same time a start of a period of new opportunities and possibilities. For me the moment to follow a few of my dreams. Including organizing baking workshops, but also realizing these 'Bed and Brownies'. In the old carpenter workshop of my father-in-law, completely renovated by Michiel, we would like to welcome you for a wonderful stay. We live right next to the studio with our children  and we are available as much as possible for your questions or a nice chat, although you can of course also retire. The studio is brand new, with beautiful new kitchen and bathroom, underfloor heating and electric auping beds for a great night's sleep. The Bed and Brownies is located directly behind the cozy marina in Scheveningen. The beach and the dunes are also within walking distance. Breakfast can be arranged in the fully equipped kitchen or can be enjoyed in one of the restaurants nearby at the harbor or in the pleasant shopping street Frederik Hendriklaan! No B of Breakfast, but Brownies, because of course I provide a delicious home baked treat on arrival.

name: 3 Bedroom Villa 200m from The Hague Beach Kijkduin
description: Whether you want a trouble free week with the whole family or a weekend away with friends, our 3 bedroom holiday home in Kijkduin The Hague (Den Haag) is the perfect get away and only 200m from Beach and Sea. Relax and unwind, take a long walk on the beach, enjoy the sea or be active and ride a bike on the most beautiful dune trails; everything is possible! A holiday in The Hague with all its cultural attractions is nearby.
neighborhood_overview:
Beach Resort Kijkduin - The Hague
Beach Resort Kijkduin borders on a wide sandy beach, at the heart of a large swathe of dunes. Not too big, not too small. Kijkduin, The Hague's second beach resort, has a very cosy feeling about it. In this charming family resort on the south side of The Hague, stylish beach pavilions provide a wealth of enjoyment for children and adults. A variety of beach clubs and restaurants on the boulevard serve organic, fresh and delicious meals. The covered terraces are open all year round and heated in the winter. Sports lovers are also in the right place at Kijkduin. The Sand Motor peninsula, especially for wind and kite surfers, makes this the ideal place to learn the sport. Enjoy the sun, sea, sand, and get a taste of freedom in Kijkduin!

Ideal holiday resort
Kijkduin is ideal for a day out and for longer holidays. The beach at Kijkduin is quiet and clean with large swathes of dunes to walk or cycle through; kite surfing is wonderful

name: Sunny house near beach and Peace Palace
description: Sunny spacious house with sheltered balcony. Minimum 2p (max 4p). Quiet neighbourhood, close to shops, caf√©s, restaurants, musea and beaches. Just 1 minute walk to tram 3 (station Den Haag CS + citycenter) and tram 12 (station Den Haag HS + beach). Just 10 m cycling to beach, Peace Palace and musea. P: yes (free  17 - 21 pm)
neighborhood_overview: Pleasant, green neighborhood with a mix of young, older, white and colored residents, cozy! Close by are lively shopping streets (Fahrenheitstraat, the Fred) with Appie, the HEMA, many cozy lunch rooms, cafes and restaurants. name: A cozy retreat minutes from the beach
description:
Cozy apartment in the well-known beach area of Scheveningen. Just 5 minutes walking from the beach!
It's a quiet area but there's always something to do and it's near all necessities.
The apartment is suited for couples, a family, working retreat, or a group of friends.
If you're into Canadian-style bbq garden parties, Michelin quality cooking, having a sip at the bar, enjoying a book in silence or just watching Netflix on the comfy couch; this apartment is for you!
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is in a quiet neighbourhood in the hip area of the Hague: the well-known Scheveningen. Within 5 minutes you can:
-Take your towel and go for a swim in the sea;
-Sip a cocktail at one of the caf√©s on the boulevard while looking at the sunset on the beach;
-Take a stroll along the Pier, where you can go bungee jumping, zip lining or hop on the Ferris wheel to see Scheveningen from up high;
-Go for a walk or run in the outstretched dunes along the beach, see if you can spot a fox!
-Find a restaurant that fits your liking on the boulevard;
-Go windsurfing at the beach;
-Sport to the swimming pool, tennis court or bowling alley;
-See a movie at the cinema, a play at the theatre or take your chances in the casino;
-Take a tram to the centre where you can enjoy a day of sightseeing (Parliament, castles, the Peace Palace, Mauritshuis museum, Maduraudam, and classic old Dutch houses) and shopping!

name: Unique Ocean view beach apartment in Scheveningen
description: Ocean view apartment right on the beach of Scheveningen next to the characteristic red lighthouse. Perfect for a beach get-away! Enjoy the sunset from our living room or step outside for a nice beach walk. Wake up to ocean sounds and ocean view from our master bedroom. Close to beach restaurants and shops.
neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is right beneath the iconic Scheveningen lighthouse built in 1875. Scheveningen has lots of beach restaurants during summer time. We are a 5 minute walk from the Scheveningen harbour with many different dining options. From luxury sushi to fish and chips.

The Hague city center is only 20 minutes away with public transport. The Hague is rich in museums with art from many famous painters like Vermeer (girl with the pearl earring) and Mondriaan.

First time visitors should have look at the next sights:
- The pier
- Beelden aan zee has beautiful sculptures
- Het gemeente museum
- Mauritshuis

There are more things to do in Scheveningen than hang on the beach all day. Visit the casino, circus theatre, the pier or the indoor mall.

If you are more into activities. Rent a bike to explore the dunes or rent a surfboard and play in the waves.
host_about: Outdoor enthousiast. Surfing and kitesurfing are my passions besides chocolate!

The house is located near the palace of the King of the Netherlands. Very extensive hiking and cycling routes through the dunes and forest area are laid out and available.

In addition, there are numerous facilities and recreational opportunities nearby, such as Park Marlot, the Hague Forest and the indoor swimming pool Overbosch.

description:
This is a very spacious and cozy family home which is very centrally located between the beach and the city. Shops, supermarkets, ATM, pharmacy, lunch rooms and restaurants can be found in this nice street.

After 8 minutes by bike you are on the beach, where you can marvel at the beautiful UNESCO world heritage dune area with forests and beaches.

neighborhood_overview: Fahrenheit has been a household name in The Hague since 1920. Every Hagenaar knows how to find the Fahrenheitstraat, and with it the Thomsonlaan and the Thomsonplein, and that is not for nothing. These shopping streets in the beloved Bomenbuurt are the place for daily shopping and shopping. Here you will still find the finest cheeses, the most delicious breads and fresh fish. In addition, there are also a butcher, greengrocer, nut farmer, liquor store, 2 beautiful supermarkets and many more nice and tasty shops in this neighborhood near the Zuiderstrand. From clothing stores to small branches of large retail chains, De Fahrenheit shopping area offers plenty of opportunities for relaxed shopping. Ready to shop? Then enjoy a snack and a drink in one of the cozy coffee shops, cafes, lunchrooms or restaurants. For anyone who wants to shop outside the city center, De Fahrenheit is highly recommended!

neighborhood_overview:
Experience the best of Scheveningen's delights just moments away from our doorstep. Sink your toes into the golden sands of Scheveningen beach, a mere 300 meters away. Whether it's sunbathing, swimming, or simply unwinding by the sea, this coastal haven offers it all.

Take a leisurely stroll along the charming boulevard, dotted with cozy beach bars and shops, offering stunning views of the sea. Indulge in the lively atmosphere of Scheveningen Harbor, where you can sample fresh seafood delights and soak in the maritime ambiance. Explore the nearby dunes by bike, encountering natural beauty and perhaps spotting Scottish Highland cattle grazing peacefully. Discover miniature wonders at Madurodam, a short distance away, or enjoy shopping along Frederik Hendriklaan's charming street. Immerse yourself in cultural and scientific experiences at Museon and Omniversum, located conveniently nearby.

neighborhood_overview:
On the beach, several nice beach tents are open from the beginning of March until after the autumn holidays where you can plunge down the dune path in a few minutes for a drink or a delicious meal. There is also a trendy beach tent in Ter Heijde that stays on the beach all year round, accessible by bike, car or on foot via the beach. On our beach there is a kiteboarding school and when there is wind you can see the kitesurfers in the lagoon or at sea doing their stunts. Also nearby is a supboard school. A good cycle path winds through the dunes towards Monster, Ter Heijde and Hoek van Holland. So there is a lot to do even when the weather is not so good. Breathing out on the beach is always good. In the park there is a well-stocked supermarket where you can walk in the morning for fresh sandwiches.
For golfers there is a challenging golf course within walking distance. The bowling alley is also accessible by foot.
The centre of The Hague and the beaches/boulevard of Sche

name: Exclusive panorama terraced residential The Hague!
description: Exclusive penthouse in the residential heart of The Hague. Beautiful and recently recycled 150 square meters apartment from the 20s. Includes radiator heating, a new Jacuzzi, a private terrace of fifty square meters and a very fast 50 Mbps internet connection that will make your stay more pleasant and even allow you to maximise your business trip. The apartment has discreet access from a staircase from the street and is fully prepared for all the needs of four guests. Superb!
neighborhood_overview:
Bezuidenhout is an affluent, elegant and high-end district located right next to the center of The Hague. This district owes its name to the fact that it is placed south of the forest of the city.

Until the 1950s, the district formed the northern boundary of the built-up area of The Hague. Art Deco is the predominant architectural style. Its elegant buildings have a height limitation of ten meters, which makes the skyline of the city visible from any point. The street names in the Bezuidenhout mainly refer to governors-general and important historical characters in The Netherlands.

Five hundred meters up north the apartment is located the official residence of the Dutch Royals, Huis Ten Bosch. Say hi to Queen Maxima and Willem-Alexander from our terrace, where you can see the dome of the palace :)
host_about:
Hello there! I'm Leo from Mendoza, the fabulous wine-growing region by the feet of the Argentine Andes. 
I studied Architecture due to its fusion with the humanist legacy of a perennial art. After graduating, I realised that high-end customer service was the exact key I needed to manage my future professional prospects, so once settled in Europe I decided to pursue and MBA in International Hospitality in the world-prestigious Hotel School The Hague.

I speak fluently five languages; I have the Cambridge Proficiency certificate in English. Spanish is my mother tongue. I am fluent in Portuguese as well. I studied French for two years, and given my Italian background, I also master the language. I am currently in a super intensive Dutch course.

I have extensive experience working in management positions for nine large multinational companies: InterContinental, Wyndham, Salomon, Hard Rock Cafe, Coldwell Banker, Royal Caribbean Int., Hertz, Louis Vuitton and MSC Cruises. The high quality standards of these companies have given me at a young age a clear vision of professional ethics.

I'm truly looking forward welcoming you in my apartment or enjoying together my personalised tours in the Benelux region!

Our dune villa is located in a fantastic spot on the coast of The Hague, in the seaside resort of Kijkduin. Close to the beach and forest. Ideal for peace seekers and kite surfers.

# atmospheric and characteristic mansion;

neighborhood_overview:
The house is located in a quiet street with little traffic.
Less than a 5-minute walk away is a village-like shopping street with restaurants and small-scale - often more luxurious shops - such as a real French bakery, organic butcher, cheese farmer, fish farmer, liquor store, etc. You can also enjoy breakfast and lunch here. This is the expat neighbourhood of The Hague with a lot of international customers.

If you walk the other direction for 5 minutes, you will reach a
lively square with terraces, several restaurants and a long shopping street. Here are the larger shops such as two larger supermarkets, Blokker, drugstore, pharmacy, etc. This is a more metropolitan area with many multicultural eateries in addition to the rural...

From home, the so-called Museum Quarter in The Hague (Statenkwartier) can easily be reached by foot. For example, the Kunstmuseum Den Haag (former Gemeentemuseum), the Museon, the Fotomuseum Den Haag and the Omniversum
host_about: My name is Danny. I am a hard-working daddy who loves to travel. Besides travelling, my favourite hobbies are sport (tennis, fitness) and reading. Especially I am interested in history. My motto is "enjoy life, it's a precious gift..."

description:

host_about:
Hi! We are Michelle and Dennis. We just renovated Dennis' apartment in Den Haag/Scheveningen (summer 2020) and are now ready for you to enjoy it!

name: Welkom in ons heerlijke Van Gogh Huisje!
description:
We warmly welcome you to come and enjoy our nice and atmospheric place! The entire cottage is at your disposal. Privacy guaranteed and fully equipped!

Within no time you are on the Scheveningen beach, the Hague city center or ride our bikes through nature!

The Cottage is about 60 m¬≤ in size , has its own front door located on a quiet side street and has 3 rooms.

It is a wonderful place to completely unwind.
neighborhood_overview:
Within no time on the Scheveningen beach, the Hague city centre or on our bikes through nature!

A PLACE WITH HISTORY
From Huygens to Spinoza.

The Huisje is located on Schoolstraat in the middle of the medieval Huygenskwartier. A stone's throw away lived and worked the leading Dutch mathematician, physicist and astronomer and inventor Christiaan Huygens.

His contemporary Benedict de Spinoza, considered one of the most influential philosophers and thinkers in Dutch history, lived in Kerkstraat.

Constantijn Huygens, the father of Christiaan, built Hofwijck in 1642. This beautiful museum is 200 metres from the cottage. A description of an interesting walk along historic houses is waiting for you.

DELICIOUS SHOPPING AND DINING
in the cozy Herenstraat at 75 m from the cottage!

Around the corner, 75 metres away, is the cosy Herenstraat with unique shops, plenty of restaurants, cafes and coffee shops. Warm baker Klin

name: Vissershuisje aan zee
description:
This is a place to unwind. To feel at home. To bathe in the bright sea light, where the air smells salty and you can hear the sound of the sea in a storm.
This is the old Scheveningen, a piece of village with its own quiet pace, the time stood still, where one still greets each other. The Vissershuisje is from 1860 at 200m from the beach.
After sunbathing, swimming, surfing, cycling or hiking you can chill out again, do some cooking or bathing or after an autumn shower you can warm up again by the fireplace.
neighborhood_overview: This is one of the only old parts of Scheveningen that is still standing. The traditional Vissershuisjes. (Fishermen‚Äôs) They are the ones behind de ‚ÄòSchippershuisjes‚Äô. (The ones for the captains...they owned the houses on the front of the street). These few old streets have lots of little unique houses and alley‚Äôs and there is hardly any traffic. The neighbors are very friendly and caring for each other. I love living here for it‚Äôs special character and feel. But most of all of course... because of the sea.

name: Spacious apt with panoramic roof terrace!
description:
Beautiful classic top floor apartment (104m2) with a stunning roof terrace (35m2)! The apartment has two bedrooms with queen size beds, a spacious living room/dinning room, separate toilet and bathroom and a private entrance.

The house is overall baby friendly. A baby changing station and crib will be located and available for use for your stay. For guests arriving with only two persons, the second bedroom will be used as storage and off limits.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located just next to the famous Frederik Hendriklaan and close to the beach! Within 5 minutes, you will arrive in the historic shopping street filled with many restaurants, small boutiques and specialty food shops. To the beach is only a 10 minute walk. There you can find a few beach bars to enjoy

Also nearby are all you basic needs such as a grocery store (4mins walk), drug store (6minutes walk), etc.

In addition to the nearby beach and inner harbour, there is two beautiful parks near by. A forrest which is a dogs "run free" park and the dune park next to the beach. From October 1st to May 1st dogs can walk off leash on the beach and for the rest of the year, dogs can be on the beach after 21:00.

host_about: Hi my name is Karijn and together with my husband and 2 daughters I enjoy living in The Hague. name: Gezellig appartement in leukste buurt van Den Haag
description:
Spacious apartment in the nicest neighborhood of The Hague, Duinoord. This bright partner home with garden has original details but is also equipped with many comforts such as wifi, and is a perfect base for a wonderful city trip.
Located between Scheveningen and Centrum, around the corner you will find numerous restaurants and shops in the cozy Reinkenstraat and Prins Hendrikstraat. The beach and city are also easily accessible by tram (10min), tram stops within 2 minutes walking distance of this property.
neighborhood_overview:
Really a nice neighborhood in a nice city: Duinoord! The space is next to the Sunny Court park with benches for reading and children's playground equipment, an oasis in the city. There are up to 4 bakeries in Reinkenstraat and at the AH across the street you complete your breakfast. For lunch we can recommend Haver and That's Amore. And Zammcaffe has the best coffee: all within a minute of walking. The nearby Sweelinck Square is one of the most beautiful squares of The Hague: taste the atmosphere of the stately The Hague of old. The nicest shopping streets to really shop are the Noordeinde and the Dennenweg. Second Chamber buildings, Mauritshuis, Museon, Madurodam are within cycling distance. Just like the sea: our favorite is the Zuiderstrand with very nice beach tents and a wide beach. For a fish you go to Scheveningen-Haven.
Parking can be paid on the other side 18-24:00 (‚Ç¨2/hour).

The neighborhood is young and diverse, located around one of the most beautiful canals of The Hague.
Many special restaurants of various cultures, terrace boats and nice cafes on and on the canal. It is a diverse neighborhood, many expats who have escaped the standard dull expat neighborhoods. This neighborhood is also popular with students, artists and artists, and the LGBTQ+ community. It is an incredibly diverse neighborhood, very safe to live or stay in and very residents are very easy to deal with and for each other. Chinatown is just around the corner and there are shops and restaurants of all cultures. Parliament and other cultural institutions are all within this neighborhood. Living, culture, food, to the park around the corner or hang out at the bar, it's all possible in this neighborhood.

name: Cosy house in Scheveningen 5 min walk to the beach
description:
The perfect location for beach lovers and surfers!
Only 5 min. from the beach, our ground floor apartment is located in a quiet and green private street. The tram stops 2 min. from the house and takes you to The Hague city center within 10 min.
The house (50m2) is cosy, with a fully equipped kitchen, bedroom with double bed and bright living room with dining area. The sunny bench in front of the house and backside patio with hammock are both relaxing spots to chill and have breakfast.
neighborhood_overview:
With a 5 min. walk to the beach and a 15 min. tram ride to the Hague City Center, this house is perfectly located in Scheveningen.
For restaurants and bars you can go to the boulevard, the port of Scheveningen, the Pier, or try out one of the many local places all around.
If you want to enjoy a nice walk in nature, you can go to the dunes, to the multiple small forests and parks nearby, and of course to the beach.
Fancy a day shopping? You'll have plenty of choice between the Badhuisstraat, the Keizerstraat and the Palace Promenade.
There are many other activities you can do in Scheveningen, like surfing, going to a musical at the Circus Theater, going to the casino, the movies or to a museum.
There is something to do for everyone!

neighborhood_overview:
Lively, yet quaint area
My house sits in the lively 'Bezuidenhout' area, straight across from a historic courtyard. A 2-min walk takes you to the Theresiastraat which is full of cafes, restaurants, grocery stores and other useful stores.
Walk another 2 minutes and you find yourself in the 'Haagse Bos', the park that used to be part of the King's palace - nowadays open to the public. This is the perfect place to unwind, go for a stroll, or seek some coolness on a hot summer day.

Beach
You have access to the beach through the Haagse Bos (25 min) or in a straight line (15 min).

Airport/Amsterdam
Train station Den Haag Laan van NOI is a 10 minute walk. Every 15 minutes a train departs to the airport (20 min) and Amsterdam (30 min).

host_about:
Hoi ik ben Amelia en run een leuke B&B in Scheveningen vlakbij het strand, Circustheater, Kurhaus en boulevard. Carpe Diem is mijn motto en ik vind het prettig als mijn gasten het naar hun zin hebben. Ik verwacht wel dat gasten rekening houden met elkaar en met de buren.

Feel like getting a breath of fresh air with a fantastic sea view? The Scheveningen boulevard and the Pier are just a stone‚Äôs throw away. You also don‚Äôt have to go far for a walk in natural surroundings. Westbroekpark and the Scheveningse Bosjes are just around the corner, where you can take a stroll, get in some exercise, paddle around in boats or enjoy festivals like Parade in spring and summer.

host_about:
OVER MEZELF
Ik ben geboren in Oekra√Øne en ben trots op mijn moederland. Sinds 16 jaar geleden woon ik in Nederland (ingeschreven op november 2015) en ben dol op de mogelijkheden die dit (ik noem het mijn) vaderland aan mensen kan bieden. Vriendelijkheid, hardwerkende mentaliteit en discipline spreken me erg aan in Nederland. Ik hou even veel van die 2 prachtige landen.

WELKOM
In mijn huis voel je je gelijk op je gemak. Voel je je thuis en vergeet niet dat je op bezoek bent is mijn motto.

HET KOKEN IN HUIS OF BUITEN HUIS OM ETEN
Het delen van keuken en eetkamer gaat hier in samenwerking met elkaar. Ik kook op vaste tijdstippen: vaak om 17:00 uur. De tijd er voor of er na kan gebruikt worden voor het bereiden van je eigen maaltijd. Het halen van een lekker buitenlands gerecht is hier makkelijk te doen. Grieks, Perzisch, Turks (Istanbul), Chinees, Indisch (Ramna), Italiaans, Japans, Surinaams, Afrikaans en natuurlijk Nederlands eten is hier vaak op 5 minuten loopafstand / makkelijk te vinden.

KOFFIE EN THEELIEFHEBBERS
Voor koffieliefhebbers is Florencia (Italian Icecream) voor de deur. Coffie Company is weer te vinden op 250 meter loopafstand van huis terwijl Boon (koffiebranderij) met verschillende soorten koffie uit verschillende landen  zich op maar 50 meter loopafstand bevindt. Het bezoeken van Lola Bikes & Coffee aan het Noordeinde zorgt zonder meer voor een onvergetelijke ervaring. 
Natuurlijk kan je ook een bakkie koffie thuis zetten met Bialetti Moka Induction mokapot voor 3 kops. Zowel koffie als thee is gratis voor gebruik. 

AUTO PARKEREN
Voor mensen die laat komen of het te druk hebben met hun planning kan geheel kosteloos een bezoekers parkeerkaart gebruikt worden. name: Smaakvolle Studio in voormalig melkfabriekje
description:
In the heart of the trendy Zeeheldenkwartier, 15 minutes from the beach in a unique industrial monument - the former dairy factory De Sierkan - you will spend the night in our completely renovated studio with designer furniture on wonderful beds from Auping!.You are a guest next to the headquarters of design magazine WOTH Wonderful Things.
The studio is located in a nice and quiet side street.The Peace Palace of Carnegy is a five minute walk away.
neighborhood_overview:
ZEEHELDENKWARTIER IS
one of the coziest city districts on the outskirts of The Hague city center. A neighborhood with many authentic shops, friendly restaurants and cafes, sunny squares and beautiful youth-style buildings can be found. No wonder that the Zeeheldenkwartier is extremely popular with locals in The Hague. In short: definitely worth a visit if you want something else!

Atmospheric squares and lively streets
The Zeeheldenkwartier was founded at the end of the 19th century when the population of The Hague grew strongly. The former rural area, largely owned by Queen Anna Paulowna, was transformed after her death into a residential area according to a right street plan with two central squares, the Anna Paulowna Square and the Prince Henry's Square. These two atmospheric squares still form the heart of the Zeeheldenkwartier. In summer, you will find numerous cozy terraces here. The two squares are surrounded by lively streets, each with its own personality.

You will find many flats and porch houses, but also a fair number of single-family houses and downstairs and upstairs dwellings. Characteristic of the neighborhood are the fourteen squares.

The Fahrenheitstraat, Thomsonlaan and Thomsonplein are the places to store and do your daily shopping. Here you will find the finest cheeses, the most delicious breads and fresh fish. You can also enjoy a snack and a drink in one of the cozy cafes or restaurants such as: Bagels & Beans, Burrata or Brasserie Beekink & Co. On the Goudsbloemlaan you will find a large supermarket and several (fresh) specialty stores.

neighborhood_overview:
Duinoord is a district in The Hague, which is part of the borough Scheveningen, situated between the Laan van Meerdervoort, Conradkade and Groot Hertoginnelaan. In the center of Duinoord the pittoresque Sweelinckplein is located, surrounded by playful and varied buildings thank to an architectural contest in the 19th century, where each architect had to design three adjacent buildings. The streets are mostly named after musicians. At the Reinkenstraat you can find many cozy lunchrooms and authentic shops. Because Duinoord is located between the city center and the beach, it‚Äôs a very popular district.
On the other hand you have the Frederik Hendrikstraat (for locals seen as ''Fred'') which is a long shopping street with all kinds of shops, basically everything what you need for your stay.

host_about:
I am a Landscape Architect, father of 3+2 children remarried to a lovely mother, living in Z√ºrich and near Paris.
I love landscapes, architecture, cities and their inhabitants in all their local varieties. I travel often for teaching, design & surveys of landscape architecture and for my pleasure with family. As traveler I either chose characteristic small hotels or book myself at private house via AirBnB and others.
Starting from my own architecture developments I am renting out since 2008.
I am your host in 3 very different architect‚Äôs houses on AirBnB with local hosts Billie & Lova,  Kurt, Sang, Justine, Paul & Andreea. 
Landscape Achitects Chalet Pigniu in Switzerland is my own design built in 2004 with DGJ Architektur and local builders. 
Landscape Architects Hofje is a former printshop housing in The Hague. It was refurbished by an architect-couple who lived there until i bought it as my private residence in 2015. In 2022 we finally got permission to rent 30 nights per year.
In Zurich i rent a dream rooftop lofty I designed it for myself but now rather stay with my wife elsewhere and with my children below. As a professional designer of living environments and sideways host I like to get inspired from other people's way of hospitaliy in an authentic manner to improve our own. As a traveler I never look for ‚Äûbest practice‚Äú or , worse ‚Äûstandard‚Äú properties - which you will probably also not find at those homes of mine. 
Until 2019 I was an estate manager of urban boutique estates Parques Guesthouses. In Kralingen Rotterdam 2014 and Rietberg Z√ºrich 2016 we provided 8 rooms each in typical local family townhouse or apartment until 2019. They where managed by my former business partner Mascha and we had up to 7 extra staff. 
You will find more host reviews on Parques in Mascha Leummens profile who now runs Parques Pico in Wassenaar on her own.

This newly renovated apartment offers a comfortable stay with a magnificent view of the skyline of The Hague. With a spacious open plan living, a sunny roof terrace with lounge set and a well-equipped kitchen, this is the perfect place for a relaxing city trip or business stay.

description:
This centrally located property is tastefully decorated and fully furnished. The house offers a living room with an open plan kitchen, 3 bedrooms one with a king size bed and two with queen beds. Luxurious bathroom with bath, separate shower and second toilet, free Wi-Fi and free parking in the street.

Close to public transport to the center, 3 minutes walk to tram 16 and tram 9 to Scheveningen is 10 minutes walk. Highways to Delft, Amsterdam and Rotterdam are nearby.

The house is in a quiet neighborhood, at the corner of newly built houses. centrally located. Public transportation is close by and takes you to various museums such as Mauritshuis, Gevangenpoort, Binnenhof & Gemeentemuseum.

name: Lovely neighbourhood, near the sea
description: Our place is located in a pleasant neighborhood with many terraces. The location is exactly between the sea and the city center of The Hague. Both are 2km, 10 minutes cycling or 25 minutes walking from our home.
host_about:
Wij wonen in een mooie bovenwoning (uit het jaar 1895) in een gezellige en rustige buurt in Den Haag. Om de hoek vind je meerdere leuke koffietentjes zoals 'Fleur's koffie' en 'Lolapalooza' ook zou je kunnen ontbijten bij het gezellige 'Pompernikkel'. Daarnaast zijn zowel het centrum als het strand slechts op 2 km afstand. Deze afstand is voor de meesten te voet of te fiets goed te doen echter zijn beide ook goed bereikbaar met het openbaar vervoer. 

Ruimte
Het bovenhuis heeft 3 verdiepingen. Op de tweede verdieping is de badkamer. De badkamer heeft naast een wastafel, toilet en douche ook een ligbad. Wij hebben shampoo en douchegel waar je gebruik van mag maken. Op de derde etage is de kamer waar je mag komen verblijven. De kamer is met een deur afsluitbaar. In de kamer zit ook een kleine wasbak. De kamer heeft een authentieke uitstraling en vooral met de regen is het slapen in deze kamer erg knus! 

Geen huisdieren
Wij hebben zelf geen huisdieren. 

Vragen?
Als je vragen hebt, stuur dan vooral een berichtje:)

description:
You are very welcome in our family home! Ideal for families with small children who want to discover The Hague and its surroundings.
The house is a fifteen-minute bike ride from the city center and beach. Around the corner you will find the tram and nearby are many shops and cozy cafes!

name: Fully renovated 2 bedroom apartment with balcony.
description:
Be right at home in this spacious apartment. Close to the forest, the beach, and the city center! The apartment is located in a residential area with lots of restaurants and amenities stores within walking distance.

The apartment has 2 bedrooms with double beds. The bedroom at the back of the house has French doors to the balcony.

There is a stylish living room and dining area with an open kitchen. The kitchen is fully equipped and here you can enter the balcony too.

Have a lovely stay.
neighborhood_overview:
The Hague, South Holland, Netherlands
The apartment is located in Bezuidenhout. This apartment is very centrally located; within walking distance of the central station and Laan van Noi station. You have the shopping street Theresiastraat around the corner where you can find many shops, supermarkets, restaurants, and cafes.
Transport options
You can use 2 bicycles. Public transport is within walking distance to the beach and the center.
host_about:
I rent out my house when I am away for work or on vacation myself. So this is my home and I want my guest to feel it is their home too during their stay. The house has all the comfort you might expect of it as I take good care of it. I only accept guest that will do that too and that respect the neighbourhood (which is amazing). 

You can expect a lot of recommendations for activities, restaurants and coffee bars in the area during your stay.

name: Villa de Grasduin vlakbij zee
description:
Be welcome at the beautiful, family-friendly Villa de Grasduin, in a unique location about 400 meters from the beach.

In the surroundings of Kijkduin Beach Resort, you can go hiking or cycling through the dunes, sunbathing on the beach, swimming in the sea or kitesurfing. For a city trip you can visit The Hague and Rotterdam.

Kijkduin Beach Resort offers amenities such as a restaurant, indoor swimming pool, padel courts and free parking.
neighborhood_overview:
Beach Resort Kijkduin The Hague
At the edge of a wide sandy beach, in the middle of a vast dune area, is Beach Resort Kijkduin; a vast, green park.
The beach within walking distance, a cozy terrace, wonderful playgrounds and an indoor pool are only a few of the many possibilities. Because the park is car-free and there is plenty of space, the children can play outside to their heart's content all day long.

Kijkduin is a pleasant seaside resort south of The Hague. Kijkduin offers something for everyone: atmospheric beach pavilions along a beautiful promenade, but also peace and nature.

There are also many opportunities for cultural excursions in the area. In The Hague you can visit the Royal Palaces, the Binnenhof with the Knights' Hall, the Second Chamber and all kinds of museums. Cities like Utrecht and Amsterdam are also easy to reach (37 and 52 minutes by train respectively).
For entertainment, a trip to an amusement park like Duinrell is alway
host_about:
Mijn naam is Ilse en als eigenaar van Villa de Grasduin heet ik je van harte welkom op een onvergetelijke strandvakantie in Den Haag.

description:
I'm renting a recently renovated room in my apartment with a small double-size bed (120x190) close to the beach, the dunes and the harbour and The Hague City Center is only a 15 minutes bike ride!
The room has private access to the shared sunny balcony with table and chairs, high speed wi-fi, 50 inch tv with streaming apps available.
Tram and bus stop 200 meters away and a big supermarket nearby.
You will share the apartment with me, my daughter and sometimes my cat, when he's not outside!
neighborhood_overview:
The area is surrounded by nature, Westduinpark, the dunes, the sea.
You can bike through the dunes, go to the beach or just hang out at one of the terraced restaurants at the harbour. Everything is at a short walking distance!

The closest and quieter beach is Zuidstrand, 600 meters away and includes a nice, short walk through the dunes. There you can find the beach club Zuid.
Zuidstrand can get very busy during summer period but it's less chaotic and touristy than Scheveningen beach, which is only anyway 2 km away.

name: NEW renovated & private Tiny House with bikes
description: NEW renovated! Atmospheric Tiny House, with two bicycles in a perfect location. The center of The Hague is a 15-minute bike ride away, the beach is just 10 min away. Ideal for a beach holiday or a weekend in The Hague, museum visits, or forest walks. Modern kitchen with fridge and oven. A shower, toilet, a double bed and a comfortable sitting area with sofa, table and chairs. Perfect for 2 to 3 people. The sofa can be folded out as an extra bed. We speak Dutch, English and German.
neighborhood_overview:
Benoordenhout is a stately neighborhood with lots of greenery in the Haagse Hout district of The Hague, built for the most part between about 1925 and 1935. The neighborhood is quiet and safe.
In this district people speak of '15 minute life' because everything can be reached within 15 minutes: the city of The Hague and the wonderful beach of Scheveningen.

Shopping
You can do a small errand on foot at shops on Willem Royaardsplein. For big shopping, the center of The Hague or the Mall of the Netherland (15 min by car) offers everything you need.

Nature
The Tiny House is located on the edge of a forest/park, and is surrounded by greenery and trees. So for a lovely walk or picnic you go to Park Clingendael; a beautifully landscaped nature park, just around the corner!

Bicycle
By bike you can easily and quickly reach one of the many museums in the area (such as: Mauritshuis, Madurodam, Louwman, Kunstmuseum Den Haag, Voorlinden, etc.) or

host_about:
I hope you are having an excellent day! 

My name is Bram and I live in the lovely beachside town of The Hague, Holland. I very much like living here because we have everything: beaches, dunes, history, city life. It is hard to leave. Only for great trip abroad maybe ;-). 

I love to surf and snowboard and practice yoga everyday. Reading is a favorite pass-time as well but my greatest passion however is music in all shapes and forms. Listening but most definetly playing and making music, both acoustic and electronic.

I am traveling for both buiness and pleasure. and looking forward to meeting you!

Bye!

Bram

neighborhood_overview: Scheveningen is a seaside resort town located in the Netherlands. It is part of The Hague and has been a popular tourist destination since the 19th century. Visitors to Scheveningen can enjoy its beautiful beaches, lively nightlife, and many attractions such as Sea Life Scheveningen aquarium, miniature golf courses, an amusement park with roller coasters and other rides, shopping centers with designer stores and boutiques as well as traditional Dutch markets selling local products like cheese or clogs. There are also plenty of restaurants offering delicious seafood dishes from freshly caught fish from the North Sea.

neighborhood_overview:
The garden house is located in a quiet green neighbourhood at 100 meters from the dunes and 400 meters from the beach. The 6 kilometres long- and 600 meters wide Westerpark touches the North Sea at the other side. The dunes dotted with small lakes, a rich flora and beach are attractive not only in summer but during all seasons when colours change hour by hour and with a rich animal and birdlife.

It is the starting point for strolls, bicycle trips to the dunes, the beach and the park between Scheveningen and Kijkduin, the Zandmotor, The Hague city Centre, and Hoek van Holland. Day trips can be made to Delft, Leiden Amsterdam and, Rotterdam. In summer there are restaurants on the beach and in winter one eats or buys food in Kijkduin at 2 kilometres or the shopping mall at 1.3 kilometres.

name: Klassiek appartement met terras
description: This centrally located apartment on the first floor of a beautiful 19th century building is tastefully furnished and equipped with all the comforts. What makes the  apartment unique, in addition to central location in the nice and bustling Zeeheldenbuurt, is the large roof terrace where there is sun all day!
neighborhood_overview:
The Zeeheldenbuurt is a neighborhood with atmospheric shopping streets full of private (special)business and unique restaurants.

Some highlights from the street:
- The best ice cream parlor in Den Haag (Piet, Artisans or Flavour)
- The best sat√© shop (The Bali cottage)
- Multiple vegetarian/vegan restaurants (Menny's Kitchen, Plenty)

A 3-minute walk away is a fun square with terraces (homemade beer and pub food at Van Kinsbergen), followed by another nice shopping street: De Prins Hendrikstraat, where you have cocktail night at By Rem / Old Fashioned on Wednesdays and Thursdays.

5 minutes on the other side of Anna Paulownaplein: the most atmospheric square in The Hague! Here you can go for breakfast, lunch, dinner and drinks at one of the cozy restaurants!

XL Supermarket at 1 minute walk, with the most photographed cheese shop in the Netherlands!

Other tourist highlights like Het Vredespaleis and De Paleistuinen

neighborhood_overview:
The Ypenburg district falls under the Leidschenveen-Ypenburg district and is located in the former agricultural area. The neighborhood is named after the farm and outdoor area Ypenburg. In 1936, the airport Ypenburg was opened in this area, which was used for both castle and military purposes. Until 1991 it was a military airbase. In 1996, the construction of ‚ÄúBuitenplaats Ypenburg‚Äù started, with the neighborhood / area "Bosweide".
The name has no historical background. During the construction of this neighborhood, the already existing forest was spared so that the neighborhood immediately got the luxurious look that was meant to be a tree-lined villa park.

The house is just a 10-minute bike ride from the beach, where you can enjoy the sun, sand, and surf. We also have bikes including 1 with a child's seat for our guests to use (for free) as well as an electric cargo bike that fits 2 kids (optional for rent).

Note: suitable for 2 adults + 2 kids max, not for 4 adults
neighborhood_overview:
The Bomenbuurt neighborhood in The Hague, Netherlands is a charming and cozy area known for its beautiful tree-lined streets and historic architecture. Located in the city's Segbroek district, Bomenbuurt is a residential area that is popular among locals and visitors alike.

The neighborhood is well-connected to the rest of the city, with excellent public transportation options, including tram and bus services. It's also within walking distance of several shops, cafes, and restaurants, making it a great place to explore and experience the local culture.

Bomenbuurt is home to several parks and green spaces, including the popular Bosjes van Poot and the Westduinpark, both of which offer beautiful trails for walking or cycling. In the summertime, the neighborhood is bustling with activity, as locals flock to the beach to soak up the sun and enjoy the vibrant beach culture.

Our home is located in a peaceful and quiet neighborhood, just a minute's walk away from a beautiful park. And, if you're in the mood for some seaside fun, the beach is just a five-minute walk away.

Our cozy space is perfect for those looking for a relaxing time, with all the amenities you need to feel at home. Enjoy a morning cup of coffee on our outdoor patio, or take a stroll through the nearby park.

And, when you're ready to hit the beach, it's just a quick walk away! Spend your days soaking up the sun, swimming in the ocean, and enjoying all the activities that the beach has to offer.

Overall, our Airbnb is the perfect spot for those looking for a peaceful getaway, with easy access to both nature and the beach.

The Visserijbuurt is a cosy neighborhood with small fishermen's homes. The small street is quite quiet, little traffic. Everything is within walking / cycling distance. The most beautiful thing is of course the sea: you can walk there in 10 minutes. Close to the corner (3 minute walk) is the Scheveningse Bos. The Westbroekpark is also very nice with playground and picnic/ playing field and tea house De Bootjes. The Meyendel dune area is beautiful for hiking and biking.
In the Keizerstraat and the harbor are cozy pubs and restaurants and nice shops. On the beach the nicest beach tents.
Also visit the Museums in Scheveningen: Beelden aan zee, Musee and Madurodam.
By bike or tram you are in 10 minutes in the center of The Hague for shops, restaurants and museums (Mauritshuis, Art Museum etc)
host_about: Gezin met 1 zoon en hond we houden van strand en zee, fietsen en surfen dus we wonen met veel plezier in Scheveningen!

I love Amsterdam because of it's many bars, restaurants, events and 'things to do', so, never boring!

name: 184 Kijkduinhuis
description: From 184 you can enjoy The Hague by the sea: rich culture, culinary enjoyment, walking and cycling in nature. The house is furnished according to its own style and fully equipped. The south-facing garden offers a lot of privacy and it is a good place to stay. In cold seasons, the wood-burning stove provides extra atmosphere. On the day of arrival you are welcome from 10 a.m. and on the day of departure you can enjoy 184 p.m. until 6 p.m.!
neighborhood_overview: 184 Kijkduinhuis is located in Kijkduinpark 5 min from the beach, sea and golf course. The city of The Hague is easily reached by bike or bus (departure at Kijkduin) for shopping and culture. In the close surroundings, you can cycle and walk well. Kijkduin has been renewed with good restaurants and stores. In Scheveningen you can get and eat fresh fish and enjoy musicals at the Circustheater. The amenities of Kijkduinpark are also accessible, see the website of Kijkduinpark. In short, there is much to do around 184!

description: Welcome to Westen family home! Located in beautiful The Hague South-West, conveniently positioned near Rijswijk, Delft & Kijkduin. name: Gezinswoning dicht bij zee!
description:
We are very happy to welcome you in our cozy cottage located 5 minutes away by bike from the quiet southern beach! There are plenty of toys for children up to about 5 years old and the dads and moms can also chill out here in our lounge area in our cozy south-facing garden!
Please note, our house is for the animal lovers only, namely Cortes, our black cat, will join you from time to time! No worries, he is the neighborhood friend and gets to eat at multiple addresses!
neighborhood_overview: Our cozy cottage is located in a cozy square with a playground for all ages! Within a 5-minute bike ride or 15-minute walk you can already settle down on the nearest beach, the southern beach far from tourism! And only a 6 minute walk to eat out in the harbor area. The north beach is a 7-minute bike ride away, 20 minutes walking, where our favorite surfshack the Shore is hosting surfboards and SUPs! There are also several parks, nature reserves in the area, the nearest is only a 6-minute walk away. There's a cozy shopping street practically right around the corner! And the city center of Den Haag can be reached in 15 minutes by bike! So you don't have to make any concessions, there is really a lot to do here!!

name: Charm marina view Scheveningen
description: Welcome to your serene getaway in Scheveningen, next to the harbor and beach. This modern apartment combines comfort and style with well-lit rooms, chic decor, and views of the marina. It features a cozy living area, a fully-equipped kitchen and a comfortable bedroom, all designed for a refreshing coastal retreat. The bathroom is compact and functional. neighborhood_overview: Scheveningen Harbour, a picturesque and bustling marina, is the vibrant heart of the Dutch coast. It's a place where the salty sea air mingles with the lively ambiance of waterfront eateries and sailing culture. As a functional port, it's dotted with boats ranging from sleek yachts to traditional fishing vessels, all bobbing gently on the shimmering waters. The harbour is not only a hub for maritime activities but also a gateway to the North Sea's treasures, offering scenic views, fresh seafood, and a unique blend of nautical charm and contemporary leisure facilities. Whether you're here to set sail, dine with a view of the setting sun, or simply take a stroll along the quay, Scheveningen Harbour encapsulates the essence of a maritime lifestyle.

name: Charmante tuinwoning nabij centrum en strand
description:
On the edge of the city center, around the corner from the lively Regentesseplein with various restaurants and shops. By bike or tram 15 minutes from the beach and 10 minutes from the center.

Stairless house located in a courtyard, closed to traffic. (private property). Entirely on the ground floor with a quiet, surrounded, garden at the rear. Tucked away from the hustle and bustle of the city. Sleep with the doors open, you won't hear the sound of traffic here.

Fast WiFi, well equipped kitchen, washer.
